  "2026-06-25T05:15:09.780Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Evidence: closed stale audit wrappers pm-5dbn, pm-srex, pm-b4cp, pm-34gb, pm-lzrq, and pm-gpea after confirming no active descendants remained and current findings are closed or represented by current backlog. Kept pm-z5nb open as an intentional coordination container, pm-28cf open because its own notes require a non-release-bearing close to avoid changelog mis-bucketing, pm-7zs0 open as recurring release-health, and pm-96wm open as a living ADR."
  "2026-06-25T05:20:58.757Z",codex-ecosystem-auditor,"Audit correction: stale-container closures were inspected but pruned from this product-fix PR to avoid changing old closed/open audit records and reclassifying unrelated historical work in CHANGELOG.md. Current intentional follow-up stays open here: pm-5dbn, pm-srex, pm-b4cp, pm-34gb, pm-lzrq, and pm-gpea need a dedicated tracker-only disposition pass; pm-z5nb, pm-28cf, pm-7zs0, and pm-96wm need explicit recurring/living rationale before closure decisions."
